                  <ellipse cx="20" cy="22" rx="12" ry="8" stroke="var(--blue-soft)" stroke-width="1.5" fill="none"/>
                  <circle cx="20" cy="16" r="4" stroke="var(--blue-soft)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                  <path d="M20 20v8" stroke="var(--blue-soft)" stroke-width="1.5"/>
                </svg>
              </div>
              <h4>Queen / Social Pheromones</h4>
              <p>
                Regulate colony behaviour in eusocial insects. The honeybee queen's mandibular
                pheromone suppresses worker reproduction and controls colony organisation — the
                classic <strong>primer pheromone</strong>.
              </p>
              <span class="pheromone-type-badge pheromone-type-badge--primer">Primer</span>
